data.title: Fresh and Fast
data.text: Always fast and fresh sandwich.  I love the friendliness of the staff and how clean the place is.  Works for me.

data.title: Freaky fast haha
data.text:
I have had probably like 5 or 6 different Sandwiches here. Vino is my favorite.  All delicious though.  One thing... I always have to order with light lettuce because it's always overloaded in my personal opinion.  Their chips are good. I like the jalapeño ones :)   
Always get a 1/4'ed pickles  :)

data.title: Good Sandwich
data.text: Wife and I have been at other Jimmy John's which we just average.  This one had friendly staff, and produced an excellent sandwich, facilities very clean.

data.title: Great sandwich, fast service
data.text: Ever since I had eaten at my first Jimmy Johns back home in GA. I no longer eat at Subway. I personally think Jimmy Johns has a much better sandwich. The bread is better than Subways, the meat is better. Over I believe the sandwich is tastier. Service was fast and the staff was friendly. Check it out for yourself.

data.title: This place is a winner
data.text: I truly believe that these folks set themselves apart from the other Quick Food/Sandwich places.  Their ingredients seem to be fresher and they hire great people who are willing to help you make eating type decisions.  Their pricing is in line with everyone else and they have delivery service.  On my scale of 1 - 10 I give them a well deserved 9 on the Sandwich Chain businesses.  Give them a try they are very, very good.

data.title: Very fast and fresh subs
data.text: Is getting a sub within 2 minutes fast enough? That's right, from the time I ordered and paid to the time I got our drinks poured and subs was just under 2 minutes. These people work like the speed of lightning. And they do deliver even just 1 sub. Have to say coming out of the parking lot the delivery drivers were even quicker than 2 minutes speeding thru the lot. Watch out for that. We ordered the California  Beach Club which was full of turkey, lots of lettuce and great avocado spread, cucumbers, tomato too. We opt out of the mayo. They have different bags of their chips to choose from and self serve beverages.The fast part about this is they only have the 1 bread/roll type which does speed it up. Although I did see some regular large sliced bread in a bin, so maybe they have changed that for some sandwiches. They do have a large choice of subs, small medium and large to choose from, all listed out with ingredients on the menu, that also speeds it up since you are ordering the exact item on the menu not walking thru a line telling them what to put on, all are with great healthy ingredients. You can tell them if you want to leave something off from what the menu says. You can't go wrong here. They do have some good looking chocolate chip cookies too. They have booths and tables. Super welcoming staff with smiles.Our favorite sub place.

data.title: Did not like the taste
data.text:
Not impressed with their sandwiches. The buns have no flavor, hard and just plan bad over all.  Staff needs a little personality .
Would go to subway, blimps or Jersey Mike's before them. People go there not for taste but something inexpensive .

data.title: One of the best sandwiches I have ever had!!!
data.text: My wife and I have been here three times since discovering this sandwich gem last month.  We have tried different sandwiches each time and each one was excellent.  Quickly prepared on fresh bread we have not been disappointed nor left wanting.  We have recommended this place to friends and will return(often).

data.title: The Best!
data.text: My husband is a huge lover of sandwiches and he is really hard to please, but he said that Jimmy Johns makes the BEST sandwiches he's ever had.  His favorite is the Big John!

data.title: Excellent sandwiches
data.text: Large selection of sandwiches all freshly made. Your order is placed and prepared in a few minutes. Take out or tables available to eat in rest Clean restrooms and store is very clean.. Easy parking with good access to Bell Road.

data.title: Nice Sandwich
data.text: I spotted this place when visiting my chiropractor next door. I'm glad I gave it a try. They do a very nice sandwich.

data.title: Good sub's, if only they could get orders right.
data.text: This place has great food, and they deliver if you live in a 1 mile radius, which isn't very far. Reason for the 3 star rating is that 50% of the time they either get my order wrong, forget half my order, or deliver to the wrong place. Just be sure to check your order before they driver takes off.

data.title: Very good and very fast service
data.text:
Stopped in on my way to the airport for a sandwich.  The place was in the process of filling about 50 box lunches for an order, we were greeted promptly and politely and served with 3 minutes or so.

The sandwiches are always fresh and very consistent.  I love their bread and crisp lettuce.  Makes the sandwich.

data.title: Good for party subs.
data.text: First time there and we ordered 4 "giant" subs for a party.  They were OK but nothing special.  Would eat there again but probably not order any more party subs there.

data.title: Not like home
data.text: During our visit to Suprise, Az. we tried this place and found it very lacking in quality and customer service. Sandwich's lack meat for one thing. Ordered a beef #2, came with 4 slices paper thin beef, a micro spread of mayo, but a ton of shredded lettuce. My #15 tuna had very little meat or mayo for a large size sub and again piled full of lettuce. It was like they were stretching their ingredients and still charging you list price. They then laid the subs on the pickup counter for us to take with but no bag to carry them in. When asked for them to be put into a bag, the kid behind counter pointed to bags stacked behind counter and told us to bag our own. Not the quality or service we are used to back in our home state. Go to Quiznos over on Grand and Reem!

data.title: go elsewhere!
data.text: As much as like the subs, the service is terrible!  I have finally stopped going due to the unprofessional and unfriendly attitude taken by the employees.  They are usually goofing around or on the phone behind the counter. The other thing that drives me crazy is if I want to order their "slim" sub, they won't let me add lettuce to it, they make me buy a different sub that comes with a ton of stuff i don't want on it, which is much higher in price.  I have asked that they just up charge me for lettuce but they won't.  Because of these reasons, i'll go to Jersey Mikes or Subway where I can get good service and put what I want on my sub!

data.title: Best subs around
data.text: As the newest player in the sub game I finally gave them a try and was really pleased on several levels.  The service was incredibly fast ... even at lunch time and the subs were fresh, loaded and tasted great, plus the price was really good too.  The #9 Italian combo is delicious and will fill up even the heartiest eater.  Good food for sandwich lovers at a great price and so fast you won't believe it.

data.title: Consistentcy
data.text: I order the same sandwich every time and every time it comes out different. They need to come up with some uniform, consistent way of measuring what they're putting in their product & training their employees accordingly. Also the last time I drank their water it was bad news,...how about filtering your water like other franchises do?

data.title: Nice upgraded subs and super fast
data.text: Nice subs, not just your generic fixins. They have the big menu on their wall and you choose from a good selection of different meats and fixins on different sandwich combos. The bread is the same on all, not airy and a nice size serving, however the items they put on the subs are different, like sprouts, avocado. Super fresh. Had the number 12 with cuc's,avocado,turkey,lettuce, tomatoes, very fresh nice size and enough fixins and meat. The staff is super fast  and the place is nice and clean with tables and some booths. Great staff all saying hi and when you leave they are all saying bye. They know the locals and the worker people and treat everyone like family. Makes you want to come back. Nice to have them in Surprise.

data.title: Great subs!!
data.text: This is a great place to get a sub!  The bread is soft but is a bit chewy.  The meats and veggies are fresh.  The staff is speedy and pleasant and when you walk in you are immediately greeted! We have eaten here many times and will continue to do so!
